run with:
    python3 -m http.server
(perhaps without the 3 depending on your python environment).
Go to http://0.0.0.0:8000/hello.html in browser to view.

making changes:
edit hello.py
hello.html is a small frontend to test pieces of hello.py, edit if required.
After installing transcrypt, run "transcrypt hello"
This generates __target__ folder, with js files.
run server to see it working!

Edits to python require recompilation and browser refresh.
Edit to html only require refresh.